docs.summary: API that allows creating / reading form submissions.

params.name: ids
params.doc: Submission IDs to mark as seen.

params.name: formId
params.doc: ID of the form to which the submissions belongs.

docs.summary: Marks form submissions as seen by site collaborators with manage submission permissions.

Confirms a submission.


You can only confirm a submission that has a `PENDING` status. The default status when a submission is created is `CONFIRMED`. You can change the default status for individual submissions using the [Create Submission](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/api-reference/wix-forms/form-submissions/create-submission) or [Update Submission](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/api-reference/wix-forms/form-submissions/update-submission) endpoints.

params.name: namespace
params.doc: Identifies the app which the form submissions belong to. For example, the namespace for the Wix Forms App is `"wix.form_app.form"`. The namespace of a submission can be retrieved using the Get Submission endpoint.

docs.summary:
Returns a list of up to 100 submissions, given the provided paging, filtering, and sorting.

You can only query submissions from a specified namespace. Use the query filter on the `namespace` field, otherwise you will receive an error.

For field support for filters and sorting, see [Form Submissions: Supported Filters and Sorting](https://dev.wix.com/docs/rest/api-reference/wix-forms/form-submissions/sort-and-filter).option

To learn about working with _Query_ endpoints, see [API Query Language](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language), [Sorting and Paging](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/pagination), and [Field Projection](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/field-projection).

Updates a submission.

Each time the submission is updated, `revision` increments by 1. The existing `revision` must be included when updating the submission. This ensures you're working with the latest submission information, and prevents unintended overwrites.
Triggered when a submission is created.
Triggered when a submission is confirmed or updated.
Triggered when a submission is deleted.

docs.summary: Form submission that was created or retrieved.

members.name: formId
members.doc: ID of the form which submission belongs to.

members.name: namespace
members.doc: The app which the form submissions belong to. For example, the namespace for the Wix Forms App is `"wix.form_app.form"`. The namespace of a submission can be retrieved using the Get Submission endpoint.

members.name: status
members.doc:
Status of the submission.
 - `PENDING`: When a submission has been created, but has not yet been recorded in the submission table of the forms dashboard. 
 - `CONFIRMED`: When a submission is recorded in the submissions table of the forms dashboard.

members.name: submissions
members.doc: Set of key-value pairs. Submission values where key is the form field and value is the data submitted for the given field.

members.name: createdDate
members.doc: Date and time the form submission was created.

members.name: updatedDate
members.doc: Date and time the form submission was updated.

members.name: revision
members.doc: Revision number, which increments by 1 each time the form submission is updated. To prevent conflicting changes, the existing revision must be used when updating a form submission.

members.name: submitter
members.doc: ID of the creator of the form submission.

members.name: seen
members.doc: Whether the submission was read by a site collaborator with permissions to manage submissions.

members.name: currentEntityAsJson
members.doc:
Since platformized APIs only expose PATCH and not PUT we can't assume that the fields sent from the client are the actual diff.
 This means that to generate a list of changed fields (as opposed to sent fields) one needs to traverse both objects.
 We don't want to impose this on all developers and so we leave this traversal to the notification recipients which need it.

members.name: id
members.doc: random GUID so clients can tell if event was already handled

members.name: entityFqdn
members.doc:
Assumes actions are also always typed to an entity_type
 Example: wix.stores.catalog.product, wix.bookings.session, wix.payments.transaction

members.name: slug
members.doc:
This is top level to ease client code dispatching of messages (switch on entity_fqdn+slug)
 This is although the created/updated/deleted notion is duplication of the oneof types
 Example: created/updated/deleted/started/completed/email_opened

members.name: entityId
members.doc:
Assuming that all messages including Actions have id
 Example: The id of the specific order, the id of a specific campaign

members.name: eventTime
members.doc: The time of the event. Useful if there was a delay in dispatching

members.name: triggeredByAnonymizeRequest
members.doc:
A field that should be set if this event was triggered by an anonymize request.
 For example you must set it to true when sending an event as a result of a GDPR right to be forgotten request.
 NOTE: This field is not relevant for `EntityCreatedEvent` but is located here for better ergonomics of consumers.

members.name: originatedFrom
members.doc: If present, indicates the action that triggered the event.

members.name: entityEventSequence
members.doc:
A sequence number defining the order of updates to the underlying entity.
 For example, given that some entity was updated at 16:00 and than again at 16:01,
  it is guaranteed that the sequence number of the second update is strictly higher than the first.
 As the consumer, you can use this value to ensure that you handle messages in the correct order.
 To do so, you will need to persist this number on your end, and compare the sequence number from the
  message against the one you have stored. Given that the stored number is higher, you should ignore the message.

members.name: fieldName
members.doc: Name of the field to sort by.

members.name: cursor
members.doc:
Pointer to the next or previous page in the list of results.

You can get the relevant cursor token
from the `pagingMetadata` object in the previous call's response.
Not relevant for the first request.

members.name: count
members.doc: Number of items returned in the response.

members.name: hasNext
members.doc:
Indicates if there are more results after the current page.
 If `true`, another page of results can be retrieved.
 If `false`, this is the last page.

members.name: next
members.doc: Cursor pointing to next page in the list of results.

members.name: prev
members.doc: Cursor pointing to previous page in the list of results.

members.name: filter
members.doc:
Filter object.
 
 See [API Query Language](https://dev.wix.com/api/rest/getting-started/api-query-language) for more information.

members.name: cursorPaging
members.doc: Cursor token pointing to a page of results. Not used in the first request. Following requests use the cursor token and not `filter` or `sort`.

docs.summary:
`NullValue` is a singleton enumeration to represent the null value for the `Value` type union. The JSON representation for `NullValue` is JSON `null`. Possible values are:
  • NULL_VALUE - Null value.

Possible values are:
  • UNDEFINED
  • PENDING
  • CONFIRMED
